column18: learning how analytics is applied in operations management and the tools used

Forecasting is a technique that uses historical data as inputs to make informed estimates that are predictive that helps the company gear up to meet future demands. It is a vital tool in operations management such that it impacts all business functions and operations decisions. Forecasting is mostly used  in predictive analytics.

Forecasts are rarely perfect and forecasting involves uncertainty. It may be hard perfect but the goal is to keep forecast errors as low as possible to arrive at close to perfect figures. Forecasts are more accurate for shorter than longer time horizons. Shorter time horizon may mean a lower degree of uncertainty because data variations are minimal for data with short coverage.
